<paper id="1564234832"><title>Enhancing Simple Power-Analysis Attacks on Elliptic Curve Cryptosystems</title><year>2002</year><authors><author org="Graz University of Technology" id="2112794742">Elisabeth Oswald</author></authors><n_citation>42</n_citation><doc_type>Conference</doc_type><references><reference>1480030470</reference><reference>1520399166</reference><reference>1523099545</reference><reference>1531102506</reference><reference>1548023999</reference><reference>1565369953</reference><reference>1584722274</reference><reference>1591209990</reference><reference>1603321026</reference><reference>1724890242</reference><reference>1838435525</reference><reference>2099317248</reference><reference>2105374413</reference><reference>2106876320</reference><reference>2117877038</reference><reference>2125065794</reference><reference>2155244510</reference></references><venue id="1127098075" type="C">Cryptographic Hardware and Embedded Systems</venue><doi>10.1007/3-540-36400-5_8</doi><keywords><keyword weight="0.57661">Elliptic Curve Digital Signature Algorithm</keyword><keyword weight="0.47325">Power analysis</keyword><keyword weight="0.42232">Discrete mathematics</keyword><keyword weight="0.45928">Markov model</keyword><keyword weight="0.41618">Computer science</keyword><keyword weight="0.43065">Algorithm</keyword><keyword weight="0.50728">Cryptanalysis</keyword><keyword weight="0.45216">Digital signature</keyword><keyword weight="0.42481">Theoretical computer science</keyword><keyword weight="0.48041">Cryptosystem</keyword><keyword weight="0.60182">Elliptic curve cryptography</keyword><keyword weight="0.50675">Elliptic curve</keyword></keywords><publisher>Springer, Berlin, Heidelberg</publisher><abstract>Recent applications of lattice attacks against elliptic curve cryptosystems have shown that the protection of ephemeral keys in the ECDSA is of greatest importance. This paper shows how to enhance simple power-analysis attacks on elliptic-curve point-multiplication algorithms by using Markov models. We demonstrate the attack on an addition-subtraction algorithm (fixing the sequence of elliptic-curve operations) which is similar to the one described by Morain et al. in [MO90] and apply the method to the general addition-subtraction method described in ANSI X9.62 [ANS99].</abstract></paper>